definition.text:
nash. To strike the teeth together, as in anger or pain; as, to gnash the teeth in rage.
GNASH, verb intransitive nash. To grind the teeth.
He shall gnash with his teeth and melt away. Psalms 11 2: 10.

1. To rage even to collision with the teeth; to growl.
They gnashed on me with their teeth. Psalms 3 5:1
6.
